                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7363b W 52/150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-18T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>303. My number 250, June 26, 4 p.m. On the 13th instant the Western Union
                    despatched a letter to Sir John Pender stating that in the event he did not
                    reply to the company’s offer set forth in the telegram above referred to it
                    would be withdrawn.</p>
                <p>Yesterday Sir John replied to the Western Union rejecting the offer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
